Are you aware that there are certain reasons why a person may feel itchy immediately after bathing? Bathing or having a shower is a naturally refreshing exercise that should keep a person’s body clean and free from germs but some people feel the otherwise after bathing, thus causing confusion and problems for them.
So in this article in line with a publication on Medical News Today, we are going to have a look at some of the reasons why some people feel itchy after bathing or having a shower. Just sit tight and enjoy this article while learning something new.
What Are The Reasons Why Some People Feel Itchy After Bathing?
1. Dry skin – this is the most common reason why people feel itchy after bathing. It happens when the water and laundry products strips the body of the natural skin oil that should keep it moist, thus causing the skin to get dry and the issue of itchy skin arises. Skin dryness is the leading cause of dry skin and if you are able to tackle the cause of the dryness, your itching will be in the past.
2. Eczema – this is a skin condition that arises due to the inflammation of the skin that can cause the body to be extremely dry. Eczema is a chronic skin condition that comes with serious itching and excessive skin dryness, people often experience more itching after bathing. If you are suffering from eczema, then that is the reason for your endless itching after bathing.
3. Your itching after bathing may also be a reaction to the laundry products you use. Some scented laundry products can cause itching after bathing especially if the person used the scented products on his or her towel. So making use of the towel after bathing may transfer some of the chemicals used in manufacturing the laundry products to the skin causing itching when the skin reacts.


